Coloration of preserved specimen (
<figureCitation id="13CC2A77FFCF2119DEFEF9668904B4D6" box="[1222,1284,1760,1784]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[156,187,1356,1378]" captionTargetBox="[171,1417,207,1315]" captionTargetId="figure-351@1.[169,1419,205,1317]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. Photographs of preserved specimen of Peristedion richardsi (KAUM–I. 127304, 197.2mm SL). Top to bottom: dorsal, lateral, and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738458" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738458/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="204">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Head, body and all fins light brown with grey vermiculate pattern posterodorsally on head, and dorsal and upper lateral bony plates. Dorsal fin edged with black. Pectoral fin with a central black spot and a black bar posteriorly. Peritoneum black. Fresh coloration unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3ED6579FFCF2119D976F8258F4FB5D2" pageId="1" pageNumber="204" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B4836F2FFCF2119D976F8258F4FB5D2" blockId="1.[820,1432,1467,2077]" pageId="1" pageNumber="204">
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCF2119D976F8258FD9B595" bold="true" box="[846,985,1955,1979]" pageId="1" pageNumber="204">Distribution.</emphasis>
Southern coast of 
<collectingRegion id="4933F810FFCF2119DE93F82588D4B594" box="[1195,1236,1955,1978]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="1" pageNumber="204">Java</collectingRegion>
and Flores Sea, 
<collectingCountry id="F3E07662FFCF2119DF40F8258F84B5F5" name="Indonesia" pageId="1" pageNumber="204">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
, and southern 
<collectingCountry id="F3E07662FFCF2119DE19F845886AB5F5" box="[1057,1130,1987,2011]" name="Taiwan" pageId="1" pageNumber="204">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF664B03FFCF2119DE40F84588F4B5F5" author="Kawai, T." box="[1144,1268,1987,2011]" pageId="1" pageNumber="204" pagination="335 - 346" refId="ref2798" refString="Kawai, T. 2016. Peristedion richardsi sp. nov. (Actinopterygii: Teleostei: Peristediidae) from Indonesian waters, with synonymy between Peristedion riversandersoni Alcock, 1894 and Peristedion nierstraszi Weber, 1913. Zootaxa 4171: 335 - 346." type="journal article" year="2016">Kawai 2016</bibRefCitation>
; this study: 
<figureCitation id="13CC2A77FFCF2119DF4AF8458F42B5D2" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[156,187,1038,1060]" captionTargetBox="[196,726,206,998]" captionTargetId="figure-330@4.[195,727,205,999]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Distributional records of Peristedion richardsi. Open and closed symbols indicate previously published and new records, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738462" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738462/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="204">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3ED6579FFCF211BD976F7838E85B517" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="206" pageId="1" pageNumber="204" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B4836F2FFCF211AD976F7838EF7B537" blockId="1.[820,1432,1467,2077]" lastBlockId="2.[156,767,1272,2077]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="205" pageId="1" pageNumber="204">
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCF2119D976F7838FB1BA33" bold="true" box="[846,945,2053,2077]" pageId="1" pageNumber="204">Remarks.</emphasis>
Examination of the Taiwanese specimen (KAUM–I. 
<quantity id="4C0F9B17FFCC211ADB2BFB7E8DCDB721" box="[275,461,1272,1296]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.273041972" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" unit="mm" value="1.273041972E8">127304, 197.2 mm</quantity>
SL; 
<figureCitation id="13CC2A77FFCC211ADBC6FB7E8E37B73E" box="[510,567,1272,1296]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[156,187,1356,1378]" captionTargetBox="[171,1417,207,1315]" captionTargetId="figure-351@1.[169,1419,205,1317]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. Photographs of preserved specimen of Peristedion richardsi (KAUM–I. 127304, 197.2mm SL). Top to bottom: dorsal, lateral, and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738458" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738458/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) showed it to be a mature female, many relatively large-sized eggs (
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211AD8A9FA9F8EA7B71E" box="[657,679,1305,1328]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">ca</emphasis>
. 
<quantity id="4C0F9B17FFCC211AD88CFA9F8EFEB71E" box="[692,766,1305,1329]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" unit="mm" value="0.9">0.9 mm</quantity>
diameter) issuing from the cloaca. The specimen was clearly assignable to 
<taxonomicName id="4CF74D71FFCC211ADB1CFADC8D92B75C" authorityName="Lacepede" authorityYear="1801" box="[292,402,1370,1394]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Peristediidae" genus="Peristedion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211ADB1CFADC8D92B75C" box="[292,402,1370,1394]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">Peristedion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, lacking teeth on the upper jaw and having the posterior pairs of bony plates in the contralateral lower lateral rows sutured along the midline, both being diagnostic of the genus as defined by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF664B03FFCC211AD83DFA3D8E8EB7FD" author="Kawai, T." box="[517,654,1467,1491]" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref2772" refString="Kawai, T. 2008. Phylogenetic systematics of the family Peristediidae (Teleostei: Actinopterygii). Species Diversity 13: 1 - 34." type="journal article" year="2008">Kawai (2008)</bibRefCitation>
. Moreover, it agreed well with the diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName id="4CF74D71FFCC211AD815FA5A8EFEB7DA" authorityName="Kawai" authorityYear="2016" box="[557,766,1500,1524]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Peristediidae" genus="Peristedion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="richardsi">
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211AD815FA5A8EFEB7DA" box="[557,766,1500,1524]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">Peristedion richardsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
given by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF664B03FFCC211ADAC1FA7A8D82B43A" author="Kawai, T." box="[249,386,1532,1556]" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" pagination="335 - 346" refId="ref2798" refString="Kawai, T. 2016. Peristedion richardsi sp. nov. (Actinopterygii: Teleostei: Peristediidae) from Indonesian waters, with synonymy between Peristedion riversandersoni Alcock, 1894 and Peristedion nierstraszi Weber, 1913. Zootaxa 4171: 335 - 346." type="journal article" year="2016">Kawai (2016)</bibRefCitation>
, having the following features: dorsal row bony plates 32; upper lateral row bony plates 37; chin barbels 22 (total); anterior edge of 4th sensory pore of rostral projection located anterior to anterior edge of premaxilla; perifacial rim prominent, originating near anterior margin of lower jaw; spatulate rostral projections separated by very narrow interspace (projection width 1.6 times in interspace) (
<figureCitation id="13CC2A77FFCC211ADAD2F9668D55B4D6" box="[234,341,1760,1784]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[156,187,1196,1218]" captionTargetBox="[415,1172,206,1156]" captionTargetId="figure-507@2.[414,1173,205,1157]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. (A) Dorsal and (B) ventral views of head of preserved specimen of Peristedion richardsi (same individual as Fig. 1)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738460" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738460/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">Fig. 2A, B</figureCitation>
), with straight margins basally on medial aspects; and upper free pectoral ray longer than joined rays.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF88667AFFCC211ADAA4FB2A88F9B6EC" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738460" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5738460" box="[156,1273,1196,1218]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738460/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" startId="2.[156,187,1196,1218]" targetBox="[415,1172,206,1156]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="8B4836F2FFCC211ADAA4FB2A88F9B6EC" blockId="2.[156,1273,1196,1218]" box="[156,1273,1196,1218]" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">
Fig. 2. (A) Dorsal and (B) ventral views of head of preserved specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="4CF74D71FFCC211AD973FB2A8801B6EF" authorityName="Kawai" authorityYear="2016" box="[843,1025,1196,1217]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Peristediidae" genus="Peristedion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="richardsi">
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211AD973FB2A8801B6EF" box="[843,1025,1196,1217]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">Peristedion richardsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(same individual as Fig. 1).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B4836F2FFCC211ADA8DF8A788AAB41B" blockId="2.[156,767,1272,2077]" lastBlockId="2.[821,1432,1272,2076]" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">
However, the Taiwanese specimen differed from the Indonesian 
<typeStatus id="544C8850FFCC211ADADCF8C48D10B574" box="[228,272,1858,1882]" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">type</typeStatus>
specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4CF74D71FFCC211ADBA7F8C48E0DB577" authorityName="Kawai" authorityYear="2016" box="[415,525,1857,1881]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Peristediidae" genus="Peristedion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="richardsi">
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211ADBA7F8C48E0DB577" box="[415,525,1857,1881]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">P.richardsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having slightly high- er counts of dorsal- and anal-fin rays (VIII, 23 dorsal-fin rays and 23 anal-fin rays 
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211ADB9BF8058DBEB5B4" box="[419,446,1923,1946]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">vs.</emphasis>
VIII, 22 and 
<quantity id="4C0F9B17FFCC211AD875F8058E82B5B4" box="[589,642,1922,1947]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.588" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" unit="in" value="22.0">22 in</quantity>
the former; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF664B03FFCC211ADAA4F8258D14B595" author="Kawai, T." box="[156,276,1955,1979]" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" pagination="335 - 346" refId="ref2798" refString="Kawai, T. 2016. Peristedion richardsi sp. nov. (Actinopterygii: Teleostei: Peristediidae) from Indonesian waters, with synonymy between Peristedion riversandersoni Alcock, 1894 and Peristedion nierstraszi Weber, 1913. Zootaxa 4171: 335 - 346." type="journal article" year="2016">Kawai 2016</bibRefCitation>
) and a vermiculate pattern on the dorsal surface (
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211ADA9DF8428CBFB5F5" box="[165,191,1988,2011]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">vs.</emphasis>
no distinct pattern; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF664B03FFCC211ADBAEF8428E12B5F5" author="Kawai, T." box="[406,530,1987,2012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" pagination="335 - 346" refId="ref2798" refString="Kawai, T. 2016. Peristedion richardsi sp. nov. (Actinopterygii: Teleostei: Peristediidae) from Indonesian waters, with synonymy between Peristedion riversandersoni Alcock, 1894 and Peristedion nierstraszi Weber, 1913. Zootaxa 4171: 335 - 346." type="journal article" year="2016">Kawai 2016</bibRefCitation>
). Ranges of dorsal and anal-fin ray numbers greater than two have been reported in other congeners (
<taxonomicName id="4CF74D71FFCC211ADB6BF7838DC3BA33" authorityName="Temminck and Schlegel" authorityYear="1843" box="[339,451,2053,2077]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Peristediidae" genus="Peristedion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="orientale">
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211ADB6BF7838DC3BA33" box="[339,451,2053,2077]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">P. orientale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4CF74D71FFCC211ADBEAF7838E5FBA33" baseAuthorityName="Gunther" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[466,607,2053,2077]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Peristediidae" genus="Peristedion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="liorhynchus">
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211ADBEAF7838E5FBA33" box="[466,607,2053,2077]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">P. liorhynchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4CF74D71FFCC211AD855F7838F5DB73E" authorityName="Alcock" authorityYear="1894" box="[621,861,1273,2077]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Peristediidae" genus="Peristedion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="riversandersoni">
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211AD855F7838F5DB73E" box="[621,861,1273,2077]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">P. riversandersoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4CF74D71FFCC211AD998FB7F882EB73E" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1938" box="[928,1070,1272,1296]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Peristediidae" genus="Peristedion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="amblygenys">
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211AD998FB7F882EB73E" box="[928,1070,1272,1296]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">P. amblygenys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF664B03FFCC211ADE78FB7E88DFB73E" author="Ho, H. - C. &amp; Chee, W. - L. &amp; Chang, C. - H. &amp; Shao, K. - T." box="[1088,1247,1272,1296]" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" pagination="37 - 55" refId="ref2713" refString="Ho, H. - C., Chee, W. - L., Chang, C. - H., and Shao, K. - T. 2013. Taxonomic review and DNA barcoding of the fish genus Peristedion (Scorpaeniformes: Peristediidae) in Taiwan. Platax 10: 37 - 55." type="journal article" year="2013">
Ho 
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211ADE53FB7F889AB73E" box="[1131,1178,1272,1296]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">et al</emphasis>
. 2013
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF664B03FFCC211ADED6FB7E8F68B71E" author="Ono, M. &amp; Kawai, T." pageId="2" pageNumber="205" pagination="117 - 131" refId="ref2949" refString="Ono, M. and Kawai, T. 2014. Review of armored searobins of the genus Peristedion (Teleostei: Peristediidae) in Japanese waters. Species Diversity 19: 117 - 131." type="journal article" year="2014">Ono and Kawai 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF664B03FFCC211AD94CFA9E8FEFB71E" author="Kawai, T." box="[884,1007,1304,1328]" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" pagination="335 - 346" refId="ref2798" refString="Kawai, T. 2016. Peristedion richardsi sp. nov. (Actinopterygii: Teleostei: Peristediidae) from Indonesian waters, with synonymy between Peristedion riversandersoni Alcock, 1894 and Peristedion nierstraszi Weber, 1913. Zootaxa 4171: 335 - 346." type="journal article" year="2016">Kawai 2016</bibRefCitation>
), and similar color variations are known in 
<taxonomicName id="4CF74D71FFCC211AD96CFABC8862B77F" authority="Weber, 1913" authorityName="Weber" authorityYear="1913" box="[852,1122,1337,1361]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Peristediidae" genus="Peristedion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nierstraszi">
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211AD96CFABC8FD5B77F" box="[852,981,1338,1361]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">P. nierstraszi</emphasis>
Weber, 1913
</taxonomicName>
(junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4CF74D71FFCC211ADF7DFABC8F9FB75F" authorityName="Alcock" authorityYear="1894" class="Actinopterygii" family="Peristediidae" genus="Peristedion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="riversandersoni">
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211ADF7DFABC8F9FB75F" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">P. riversandersoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF664B03FFCC211AD994FADC883FB75C" author="Ho, H. - C. &amp; Chee, W. - L. &amp; Chang, C. - H. &amp; Shao, K. - T." box="[940,1087,1369,1394]" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" pagination="37 - 55" refId="ref2713" refString="Ho, H. - C., Chee, W. - L., Chang, C. - H., and Shao, K. - T. 2013. Taxonomic review and DNA barcoding of the fish genus Peristedion (Scorpaeniformes: Peristediidae) in Taiwan. Platax 10: 37 - 55." type="journal article" year="2013">
Ho 
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211AD9EBFADC8FFEB75F" box="[979,1022,1369,1393]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">et al</emphasis>
. 2013
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF664B03FFCC211ADE72FADF88C4B75F" author="Kawai, T." box="[1098,1220,1369,1393]" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" pagination="335 - 346" refId="ref2798" refString="Kawai, T. 2016. Peristedion richardsi sp. nov. (Actinopterygii: Teleostei: Peristediidae) from Indonesian waters, with synonymy between Peristedion riversandersoni Alcock, 1894 and Peristedion nierstraszi Weber, 1913. Zootaxa 4171: 335 - 346." type="journal article" year="2016">Kawai 2016</bibRefCitation>
), suggesting that the above variations in 
<taxonomicName id="4CF74D71FFCC211ADE39FAFD8871B7BC" authorityName="Kawai" authorityYear="2016" box="[1025,1137,1402,1426]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Peristediidae" genus="Peristedion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="richardsi">
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211ADE39FAFD8871B7BC" box="[1025,1137,1402,1426]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">P. richardsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are simply intraspecific. Although, the Taiwanese specimen also differed from the 
<typeStatus id="544C8850FFCC211ADF54FA1D8998B79D" box="[1388,1432,1435,1459]" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">type</typeStatus>
specimens in 16 of 23 morphometric characters, such were likely due to ontogenetic proportional changes, the present specimen (
<quantity id="4C0F9B17FFCC211AD99CFA7A8809B43A" box="[932,1033,1532,1556]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.972" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" unit="mm" value="197.2">197.2 mm</quantity>
SL) being much larger than the other known specimens (
<quantity id="4C0F9B17FFCC211AD9CFF99A887BB41A" box="[1015,1147,1564,1588]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2349999999999999" metricValueMax="1.3199999999999998" metricValueMin="1.15" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" unit="mm" value="123.5" valueMax="132.0" valueMin="115.0">115–132 mm</quantity>
SL).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B4836F2FFCC211AD976F9BB8817B5D2" blockId="2.[821,1432,1272,2076]" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">
<taxonomicName id="4CF74D71FFCC211AD976F9BB881AB47B" authorityName="Kawai" authorityYear="2016" box="[846,1050,1597,1621]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Peristediidae" genus="Peristedion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="richardsi">
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211AD976F9BB881AB47B" box="[846,1050,1597,1621]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">Peristedion richardsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4CF74D71FFCC211ADEE3F9B88964B47B" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1938" box="[1243,1380,1597,1621]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Peristediidae" genus="Peristedion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="amblygenys">
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211ADEE3F9B88964B47B" box="[1243,1380,1597,1621]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">P. amblygenys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, distributed in the East 
<collectingCountry id="F3E07662FFCC211ADE3CF9D88842B458" box="[1028,1090,1630,1654]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">China</collectingCountry>
and South 
<collectingCountry id="F3E07662FFCC211ADE83F9D888F9B458" box="[1211,1273,1630,1654]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">China</collectingCountry>
seas, including Taiwanese waters, and the Indian Ocean off 
<collectingCountry id="F3E07662FFCC211ADF3BF9F88967B4B8" box="[1283,1383,1662,1686]" name="Indonesia" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF664B03FFCC211ADF4EF9F88FA1B499" author="Ho, H. - C. &amp; Chee, W. - L. &amp; Chang, C. - H. &amp; Shao, K. - T." pageId="2" pageNumber="205" pagination="37 - 55" refId="ref2713" refString="Ho, H. - C., Chee, W. - L., Chang, C. - H., and Shao, K. - T. 2013. Taxonomic review and DNA barcoding of the fish genus Peristedion (Scorpaeniformes: Peristediidae) in Taiwan. Platax 10: 37 - 55." type="journal article" year="2013">
Ho 
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211AD90DF9198F60B499" box="[821,864,1695,1719]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">et al</emphasis>
. 2013
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF664B03FFCC211AD994F9198889B499" author="Ono, M. &amp; Kawai, T." box="[940,1161,1695,1719]" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" pagination="117 - 131" refId="ref2949" refString="Ono, M. and Kawai, T. 2014. Review of armored searobins of the genus Peristedion (Teleostei: Peristediidae) in Japanese waters. Species Diversity 19: 117 - 131." type="journal article" year="2014">Ono and Kawai 2014</bibRefCitation>
), both having the anterior edge of the 4th rostral projection sensory pore anterior to the anterior edge of the premaxilla, a prominent perifacial rim originating near the anterior lower-jaw margin, and rostral projections with a straight basal margin on the medial aspects (
<bibRefCitation id="EF664B03FFCC211AD9B5F8C7880DB577" author="Kawai, T." box="[909,1037,1857,1881]" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" pagination="335 - 346" refId="ref2798" refString="Kawai, T. 2016. Peristedion richardsi sp. nov. (Actinopterygii: Teleostei: Peristediidae) from Indonesian waters, with synonymy between Peristedion riversandersoni Alcock, 1894 and Peristedion nierstraszi Weber, 1913. Zootaxa 4171: 335 - 346." type="journal article" year="2016">Kawai 2016</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName id="4CF74D71FFCC211ADEB1F8C488FAB577" authorityName="Kawai" authorityYear="2016" box="[1161,1274,1857,1881]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Peristediidae" genus="Peristedion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="richardsi">
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211ADEB1F8C488FAB577" box="[1161,1274,1857,1881]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">P. richardsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguishable from 
<taxonomicName id="4CF74D71FFCC211AD99AF8E5882DB554" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1938" box="[930,1069,1890,1914]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Peristediidae" genus="Peristedion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="amblygenys">
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211AD99AF8E5882DB554" box="[930,1069,1890,1914]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">P. amblygenys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having spatulate rostral projections (
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211AD94EF8058F90B5B4" box="[886,912,1923,1946]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">vs.</emphasis>
triangular in 
<taxonomicName id="4CF74D71FFCC211ADE24F80588A4B5B4" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1938" box="[1052,1188,1922,1946]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Peristediidae" genus="Peristedion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="amblygenys">
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211ADE24F80588A4B5B4" box="[1052,1188,1922,1946]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">P. amblygenys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) with a very narrow interspace, the projection width 1.33–1.73 times in interspace (
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211AD905F8428F58B5F5" box="[829,856,1988,2011]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">vs.</emphasis>
moderate interspace, projection width 
<quantity id="4C0F9B17FFCC211ADECAF8458971B5F5" box="[1266,1393,1987,2011]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4638" metricValueMax="2.7432" metricValueMin="2.1844" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" unit="in" value="0.97" valueMax="1.08" valueMin="0.86">0.86–1.08 in</quantity>
interspace; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF664B03FFCC211AD9ABF862880CB5D2" author="Kawai, T." box="[915,1036,2020,2044]" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" pagination="335 - 346" refId="ref2798" refString="Kawai, T. 2016. Peristedion richardsi sp. nov. (Actinopterygii: Teleostei: Peristediidae) from Indonesian waters, with synonymy between Peristedion riversandersoni Alcock, 1894 and Peristedion nierstraszi Weber, 1913. Zootaxa 4171: 335 - 346." type="journal article" year="2016">Kawai 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B4836F2FFCC211BD976F7828E85B517" blockId="2.[821,1432,1272,2076]" lastBlockId="3.[156,767,1792,1849]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="206" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">
Since 
<taxonomicName id="4CF74D71FFCC211AD9B2F7838FF7BA32" authorityName="Kawai" authorityYear="2016" box="[906,1015,2052,2076]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Peristediidae" genus="Peristedion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="205" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="richardsi">
<emphasis id="B983EAE0FFCC211AD9B2F7838FF7BA32" box="[906,1015,2052,2076]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">P.richardsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recorded only from Indonesian waters (
<bibRefCitation id="EF664B03FFCD211BDAD2F8868D65B536" author="Kawai, T." box="[234,357,1792,1816]" pageId="3" pageNumber="206" pagination="335 - 346" refId="ref2798" refString="Kawai, T. 2016. Peristedion richardsi sp. nov. (Actinopterygii: Teleostei: Peristediidae) from Indonesian waters, with synonymy between Peristedion riversandersoni Alcock, 1894 and Peristedion nierstraszi Weber, 1913. Zootaxa 4171: 335 - 346." type="journal article" year="2016">Kawai 2016</bibRefCitation>
), the Taiwanese specimen represents the first Northern Hemisphere record of the species.
</paragraph>
